## ⚠️ CRITICAL: Header & Sidebar logo → Admin dashboard (home)

**MUST** make the **admin branding logo** (header bar + sidebar) navigate to the **admin home (dashboard)**:

- ✅ **Target href:** `/adminWeb` — see `src/app/adminWeb/page.tsx` (`DashboardPageView` inside `AdminLayout`).
- ✅ **Implementation:** Wrap the logo (or logo + title row) in Next.js `<Link href="/adminWeb">`, **or** `useRouter().push("/adminWeb")` with keyboard-accessible semantics (e.g. `button` + `aria-label` if not using `Link`).

**MUST** keep the same behavior in both chrome areas when both exist:

- ✅ `src/widgets/adminWeb/header/Header.tsx` — `header-logo-mobile` (top bar logo).
- ✅ `src/widgets/adminWeb/sidebar/Sidebar.tsx` — `sidebar-header` / `sidebar-logo` (sidebar logo).

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Leave the logo as a **non-interactive `<div>` + `<img>` only** — users expect “logo = home”. **No build error** (silent UX bug).
- ❌ Link the logo to **removed user routes** (e.g. `/userWeb`) — admin-only product uses `/adminWeb` only.

**Checklist:**

- [ ] Header logo click navigates to `/adminWeb` (dashboard).
- [ ] Sidebar logo click navigates to `/adminWeb` (on mobile, call existing `onClose` after navigation if the drawer should close).
- [ ] If `/adminWeb/login` (or similar) shows a logo **intentionally** not linked to home, document the reason in code or rules.

