## 🎨 Styling Rules (Admin Web)

### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Custom CSS Import

**MUST ALWAYS import required Custom CSS files when:**

- ✅ Creating new admin list pages (with search forms)
- ✅ Creating new admin pages with tables
- ✅ Referencing existing admin pages as patterns
- ✅ Using custom CSS classes (e.g., `search-form-label`, etc.)

**MUST ensure required CSS files are imported:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Import required CSS files
'use client';

import React from 'react';
import { useProgramList } from '../model';
import '@/shared/styles/admin/search-form.css'; // ✅ For search forms
import '@/shared/styles/admin/mobile-table.css'; // ✅ For tables
import '@/shared/styles/admin/resizable-table.css'; // ✅ For resizable tables
// ❌ REMOVED: import "@/shared/styles/admin/table-filter.css"; // Table filters are NOT used (all filtering is server-side only)
```

**Common CSS Files for Admin Pages:**

- `@/shared/styles/admin/search-form.css` - Search form styles (required for search forms)
- `@/shared/styles/admin/mobile-table.css` - Mobile table styles
- `@/shared/styles/admin/resizable-table.css` - Resizable table styles
- ❌ `@/shared/styles/admin/table-filter.css` - NOT USED (table filters are not used; all filtering is server-side only)
- `@/shared/styles/admin/dialog.css` - Dialog styles
- `@/shared/styles/admin/sidebar.css` - Sidebar styles
- `@/shared/styles/admin/layout.css` - Layout styles

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ **NEVER** forget to import required CSS files
- ❌ **NEVER** assume CSS will work without import
- ❌ **NEVER** copy admin page code without copying CSS imports
- ❌ **NEVER** skip CSS import verification when referencing existing pages

**Why this is CRITICAL:**

Custom CSS files must be imported to apply styles. Without imports:

1. ❌ Custom CSS classes won't have styles applied
2. ❌ UI elements will appear unstyled or broken
3. ❌ Text alignment, spacing, and layout will be incorrect
4. ❌ No build errors will occur (silent failure)

**Real-world example of the mistake:**

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG: Missing CSS import
"use client";

import React from "react";
import { useMenuMakeList } from "../model";
// ❌ Missing: import "@/shared/styles/admin/search-form.css";

export const MenuMakePageView: React.FC = () => {
  return (
    <label className="search-form-label">검색구분</label>
    // ❌ search-form-label class has no styles without CSS import!
  );
};
```

**Prevention Checklist (MUST verify when creating/modifying admin pages):**

- [ ] **Checked existing admin pages** for required CSS imports
- [ ] **All required CSS files are imported** (search-form.css, mobile-table.css, etc.)
- [ ] **CSS imports are placed at the top** after React imports
- [ ] **Referenced existing admin page** (e.g., ProgramListPageView) as pattern
- [ ] **Verified CSS files exist** in `src/shared/styles/admin/`
- [ ] **Tested the page** to ensure styles are applied

**Reference Implementation:**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: src/features/adminWeb/program/list/ui/ProgramListPageView.tsx
'use client';

import React from 'react';
import { useRouter } from 'next/navigation';
import { Pagination } from '@/shared/ui/adminWeb';
import { ConfirmDialog } from '@/shared/ui/adminWeb';
import { useProgramList } from '../model';
import '@/shared/styles/admin/mobile-table.css';
import '@/shared/styles/admin/resizable-table.css';
// ❌ REMOVED: import "@/shared/styles/admin/table-filter.css"; // Table filters are NOT used (all filtering is server-side only)
import '@/shared/styles/admin/search-form.css'; // ✅ Required for search forms
```

