## Register Form Grid: `FormField` Row Boundaries & Empty Half-Cells

### Purpose (scope)

**Use this section when:**

- ✅ Building or changing **admin registration/edit** forms that use `@/shared/ui/adminWeb/form/FormField` + `@/shared/styles/admin/register-form.css`.
- ✅ A row contains **only one `md:w-1/2` field** (half row) and the next row is **`fullWidth`**, or the first row must show a **closed table grid** (including the right vertical edge) without a second real field.

**Out of scope:** Validation error DOM placement (see `admin-web-validation-ui-rules.mdc`). This section is **layout and border continuity only**.

---

### Why this is CRITICAL (failure mode)

1. **Half row then `fullWidth` row:** A half-width `FormField` draws **bottom borders only across its own 50% wrapper**. The following `fullWidth` row does **not** extend that line across the remaining 50% by default → the horizontal separator **appears broken** above the full-width row.
2. **Half row with no right cell:** If only one half-width `FormField` exists in a `flex flex-wrap` row, the **right 50% has no bordered cell** → missing **outer right vertical** and inconsistent grid vs. the row below.

**Do not rely on one-off Tailwind borders** (`border-r`, negative margins, etc.) to “draw lines” unless the product explicitly requires a custom layout. Prefer **`FormField`’s documented props** and the **empty-label half-cell pattern** below.

---

### Pattern A — Half-width row followed by `fullWidth` row (full-width horizontal rule)

**MUST** restore a **single** horizontal boundary between the half row and the `fullWidth` row using `FormField` props (see `FormField.tsx`: `suppressBottomBorder`, `forceTopBorder`).

**On the last field(s) of the row above the `fullWidth` row:**

- ✅ Set **`suppressBottomBorder`** on every `FormField` in that row that should **not** stack a second line against the next row’s top.

**On the first `fullWidth` `FormField` of the next row:**

- ✅ Set **`forceTopBorder`** so the next row’s label and field cells get **`borderTop: 1px solid #dee2e6`** across the **full** width.

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Add a raw `<div className="border-t …">` between rows **without** removing the overlapping half-row bottom borders first (risk of **double-thick** line on the overlapping segment).
- ❌ Use `forceTopBorder` alone while leaving the half-row’s bottom borders on (same double-line risk on the left overlap).

**Minimal example (conceptual):**

```tsx
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  <FormField
    label="Name"
    isFirstRow
    isFirstInRow
    suppressBottomBorder
    /* … */
  >
    <FormInput /* … */ />
  </FormField>
  {/* Optional: empty half-cell Pattern B in the same row */}
</div>
<div className="flex flex-wrap">
  <FormField label="Address" required fullWidth forceTopBorder /* … */>
    {/* … */}
  </FormField>
</div>
```

---

### Pattern B — Empty right half-cell (grid closure, no fake `FormInput`)

When the design keeps **only one real half-width field** in the first column but the **table grid must close** (right vertical edge, same row height, aligned `suppressBottomBorder` with Pattern A):

**MUST** add a second **`FormField`** in the same `flex flex-wrap` row using the **empty-label branch** of `FormField`:

- ✅ Pass a label that is **empty after `trim()`** (e.g. `label=" "` — a single space). That triggers the branch where **no label column** is rendered and the cell is **`w-full md:w-1/2`** with standard `register-form-mobile-field` borders (`FormField.tsx`, `if (!label.trim()) { … }`).
- ✅ Set **`isFirstInRow`** on this second `FormField` (same as other two-column rows, e.g. `ProgramRegisterForm.tsx`).
- ✅ If Pattern A applies to this row, set **`suppressBottomBorder`** on this empty half-cell **as well** so both halves stay visually consistent with the next row’s `forceTopBorder`.
- ✅ Put **non-visual** content only inside the cell (e.g. `<span className="sr-only">…</span>`) — **do not** add a read-only fake text input unless the product explicitly requires it.

**MUST NOT:**

- ❌ Leave the right 50% of the row **without** any `FormField` when the rest of the form uses the **two-column register grid** and the design expects a closed rectangle for that row.
- ❌ Use `label=""` if your bundler or linter strips it; use `label=" "` (space) so `!label.trim()` remains true.

**Minimal example:**

```tsx
<FormField label=" " isFirstInRow suppressBottomBorder>
  <span className="sr-only">No additional field in this column</span>
</FormField>
```

---

### Verification checklist (run before PR / handoff)

- [ ] **Row transition:** If row *n* is half-width only and row *n+1* is `fullWidth`, half-row `FormField`s use **`suppressBottomBorder`** and the first `fullWidth` `FormField` uses **`forceTopBorder`**.
- [ ] **Right edge:** If row *n* has a single half-width field but the grid must close, a second **`FormField`** with **`label=" "`** (empty after trim) + **`isFirstInRow`** (+ optional **`suppressBottomBorder`**) exists in the same `flex flex-wrap` row.
- [ ] **No duplicate lines:** No stacked `border-top` + `border-bottom` on the same horizontal segment without intentional design.
- [ ] **Reference read:** Opened `src/shared/ui/adminWeb/form/FormField.tsx` and confirmed prop behavior for `suppressBottomBorder`, `forceTopBorder`, and `!label.trim()`.

---

### Decision tree

```
Register form row uses FormField + register-form.css?
├─ Next row is fullWidth while current row has only one half-width field?
│  └─ YES → Apply Pattern A (suppressBottomBorder on current row fields, forceTopBorder on next fullWidth FormField)
└─ Same row must show a closed grid on the right but no second business field?
   └─ YES → Apply Pattern B (second FormField with label=" ", isFirstInRow, optional suppressBottomBorder, sr-only child)
```

---

