### 📁 File Type Icon Mapping (Extension → Icon)

**MUST use this mapping for `getFileIconSrc(fileName)` so all admin pages show the same icons:**

| Extension(s)             | Icon file             |
| ------------------------ | --------------------- |
| gif, jpg, jpeg, png, bmp | `ico_file_img.png`    |
| xls, xlsx, xlsm          | `ico_file_xlsx.png`   |
| pdf                      | `ico_file_pdf.png`    |
| pptx                     | `ico_file_ppt.png`    |
| hwp, hwpx                | `ico_file_hwp.png`    |
| (default)                | `ico_file_new_20.png` |

**Base path:** `/images/adminWeb/icon` (under `public/`).

**Extract extension:** lowercase, strip query string if present (e.g. `file.pdf?x=1` → `pdf`).

**Reference implementation:**

```typescript
const getFileIconSrc = (fileName: string): string => {
  const ext =
    (fileName || '').toLowerCase().match(/\.([a-z0-9]+)(?:\?.*)?$/)?.[1] ?? '';
  const base = '/images/adminWeb/icon';
  if (['gif', 'jpg', 'jpeg', 'png', 'bmp'].includes(ext))
    return `${base}/ico_file_img.png`;
  if (['xls', 'xlsx', 'xlsm'].includes(ext)) return `${base}/ico_file_xlsx.png`;
  if (ext === 'pdf') return `${base}/ico_file_pdf.png`;
  if (ext === 'pptx') return `${base}/ico_file_ppt.png`;
  if (['hwp', 'hwpx'].includes(ext)) return `${base}/ico_file_hwp.png`;
  return `${base}/ico_file_new_20.png`;
};
```

