#### 📋 Verification checklist (common file patterns)

**Before implementing or changing file upload in an admin form:**

- [ ] **State:** Register form has only a “selected/pending” list; edit form has both “existing” and “selected/pending” and they are not mixed.
- [ ] **Submit:** FormData is used; existing group id is sent on update when required; new files use the API’s field name.
- [ ] **After update:** On success, refetch then clear the pending/selected list so the UI does not show duplicates.
- [ ] **Limit (if applicable):** Remaining count = feature’s max − existing − selected; new selections are capped to remaining.
- [ ] **Detail/edit per-file delete:** After deleting an existing attachment, the user stays on the same page; success message close does not trigger list navigation unless the product rule is “save success only → list”.
- [ ] **Support register/update MessageDialog:** Title is short; success body defaults to `정상적으로 등록되었습니다.` / `정상적으로 수정되었습니다.` style without repeating the business type name; `response.result === "00"` before success.
- [ ] **Application register/detail save dialog:** Detail mode uses `수정 완료` + `정상적으로 수정되었습니다.` (or `response.message`), not only `저장 완료` / `저장되었습니다.`; register mode uses `등록 완료` tone (see §7).
- [ ] **Application save success confirm:** After OK on success dialog, navigate to **사업별 신청목록 상세** (same as cancel from that screen), not staying on the edit form unless explicitly documented as an exception.
- [ ] **Application attachment delete:** Confirm dialog before delete API; **delete success dialog** (`삭제 완료` / `정상적으로 삭제되었습니다.`); no list navigation on delete success.
- [ ] **Mentor list row delete:** After API or local-only remove, show `삭제 완료` / `정상적으로 삭제되었습니다.` success dialog (see §7 Mentor list).

---

#### 🔍 Decision tree (common file patterns)

```
Implementing file upload in admin?
├─ Is this a register form?
│  └─ YES → Single state: selected/pending files only. Submit as FormData with API’s new-files field name.
├─ Is this an edit/detail form?
│  └─ YES → Two states: existing (from API) + selected (pending). Submit FormData with existing group id (if API requires) + new files. After success, refetch then clear selected.
├─ Does the feature have a file count limit?
│  └─ YES → remaining = featureMax − existing.length − selected.length; allow only remaining new files.
├─ Per-file delete on detail/edit?
│  └─ YES → Do not navigate to list on delete success; only close message / update local state (see §5).
└─ Reference: ArticleRegisterForm (register), ArticleDetailForm + useArticleDetail (edit).
```

---

